        <lg xml:id="block_A" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2Fe412f548-06bd-43c1-9116-f2e0176da553.jp2/1128,1049,2175,2591/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>I BEGIN WITH A PRAYER of gratitude</l>
          <l>for all that is holy in my life.</l>
          <l>God needs no words, no English or Hebrew,</l>
          <l>no semantics and no services.</l>
          <l>But I need them.</l>
          <l>Through prayer, I can sense my inner strength,</l>
          <l>my inner purpose,</l>
          <l>my inner joy, my capacity to love.</l>
          <l>As I reach upward in prayer,</l>
          <l>Creator.</l>
          <l>I sense these qualities in my</l>
          <l>To love God is to love each other,</l>
          <l>to work to make our lives better.</l>
          <l>To love God is to love the world God created</l>
          <l>and to work to perfect it.</l>
          <l>To love God is to love dreams of peace and joy</l>
          <l>that illumine all of us,</l>
          <l>and to bring that vision to life.</l>
        </lg>
